name: Papadzules | Mayan Lords Food
description: Papadzules are a traditional dish of the Gastronomy of Yucatan, in Mexico. The name means, according to some Mayans, the master's food. It looks like a traditional taco stuffed with hard-boiled egg, topped with "pepita" and tomato sauce.
